## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This FSD specifies the functional behavior required to fix the tool\_use\_id mismatch bug in the kiro-ts Anthropic converter module. It defines the use cases, data flow, processing logic, and acceptance criteria that developers will implement to restore the ReAct tool-calling loop in the Chat Panel.

### 1.2 Scope

* Fix the Anthropic converter to pass through tool\_use\_id values without transformation
* Ensure conversation history stores the same ID that is streamed to the client
* Ensure continuation requests can match tool results to history entries
* Add diagnostic logging for tool\_use\_id at transformation boundaries
* Add improved error reporting when ID mismatch occurs

### 1.3 Definitions & Acronyms

| Term | Definition |
| --- | --- |
| ReAct Loop | Reasoning + Acting pattern: model reasons, calls tool, observes result, continues until done |
| tool\_use\_id | Unique identifier assigned by Kiro Q API to each tool invocation in a response |
| Continuation Request | Follow-up HTTP request containing tool execution results, sent after local tool execution |
| Anthropic Converter | Module in kiro-ts that transforms between Kiro Q internal message format and Anthropic-compatible streaming format |
| Orphan tool\_result | A tool result message whose toolUseId cannot be matched to any stored tool\_use\_id in conversation history |
| Conversation History | In-memory message list maintained by kiro-ts for multi-turn context management |
| Streaming Response | Server-Sent Events (SSE) stream sent from kiro-ts to VS Code extension client |

