## 2. System Overview

### 2.1 System Context Diagram

System Context [*Edit in draw.io*](diagrams/system-context.drawio)

The kiro-ts service operates as a middleware proxy between the VS Code extension (client) and the Kiro Q API (backend). Key interactions:

* **VS Code Extension**: Sends chatWithTools requests, receives SSE streaming responses, sends continuation requests with tool results
* **Kiro Q API**: Receives formatted requests, returns tool\_use responses with unique tool\_use\_id values
* **Conversation History (in-memory)**: Stores assistant messages including tool\_use blocks for multi-turn correlation

### 2.2 System Architecture

The fix targets the **Anthropic Converter** module within kiro-ts:

VS Code Extension <──SSE──> kiro-ts (handlers.ts)
 │
 ├── Anthropic Converter (converter.ts) ← FIX HERE
 │ ├── Request conversion (Extension → Kiro Q format)
 │ ├── Response conversion (Kiro Q → Streaming format)
 │ └── ID mapping logic ← ROOT CAUSE
 │
 ├── Conversation History (in-memory store)
 │
 └──HTTP──> Kiro Q API

## 3. Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Feature: tool\_use\_id Passthrough Fix

**Source:** BRD Story 1 — Fix tool\_use\_id Consistency in ReAct Loop

#### 3.1.1 Description

The Anthropic converter MUST pass through the tool\_use\_id value from the Kiro Q API response without modification. The same value must appear in three locations: (1) the SSE streaming response sent to the extension, (2) the conversation history stored in kiro-ts, and (3) the continuation request received back from the extension. Currently, the converter generates or maps a different ID during response conversion, causing a mismatch at step (3).

#### 3.1.2 Use Case: Successful ReAct Tool Loop

**Use Case ID:** UC-1 **Actor:** Developer (via VS Code Extension) **Preconditions:** Chat Panel is open, kiro-ts is running, Kiro Q API is accessible **Postconditions:** Tool is executed and result is incorporated into conversation; model continues reasoning

**Main Flow:**

| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Developer sends chat message requiring tool use |  | User types message in Chat Panel and sends |
| 2 |  | Extension packages chatWithTools request | Extension creates request with message history and tool definitions |
| 3 |  | kiro-ts converter transforms to Kiro Q format | Request converted from Anthropic format to internal format |
| 4 |  | kiro-ts forwards to Kiro Q API | HTTP POST to backend |
| 5 |  | Kiro Q API returns tool\_use response with id=tooluse\_XYZ | Response contains content block type=tool\_use |
| 6 |  | kiro-ts converter transforms to streaming format, preserving tool\_use\_id=tooluse\_XYZ | **CRITICAL: ID must be identical** |
| 7 |  | kiro-ts stores assistant message with tool\_use\_id=tooluse\_XYZ in history | History entry matches streamed ID |
| 8 |  | Extension receives streaming response, identifies tool call | Parses tool\_use block from SSE events |
| 9 | Extension executes tool locally |  | Tool runs (e.g., readFile, grep\_search) |
| 10 |  | Extension sends continuation with toolResult.toolUseId=tooluse\_XYZ | Continuation request sent to kiro-ts |
| 11 |  | kiro-ts matches tooluse\_XYZ in history — SUCCESS | Finds corresponding tool\_use entry |
| 12 |  | kiro-ts constructs next API request with tool\_result | Builds valid Kiro Q API request |
| 13 |  | Kiro Q API processes and returns next response | May be text or another tool\_use |
| 14 |  | Cycle repeats (steps 5-13) or model returns final text | Loop ends when no more tool calls |

Sequence - ReAct Tool Loop [*Edit in draw.io*](diagrams/sequence-react-loop.drawio)

**Alternative Flows:**

| ID | Condition | Steps |
| --- | --- | --- |
| AF-1 | Multiple tool\_use blocks in single response | Each block gets its own tool\_use\_id; all IDs preserved independently. Extension sends continuation with ALL tool results in order. |
| AF-2 | Model returns final text (no tool\_use) | No tool execution needed. Response streamed directly to extension. Loop ends. |
| AF-3 | Tool execution returns error | Extension sends toolResult with error content. kiro-ts forwards error as tool\_result to API. Model handles gracefully. |

**Exception Flows:**

| ID | Condition | Steps |
| --- | --- | --- |
| EF-1 | tool\_use\_id mismatch (current bug) | kiro-ts cannot find ID in history → logs WARNING with received ID + available IDs → returns descriptive error to extension → extension shows error to user |
| EF-2 | Kiro Q API returns tool\_use without id field | kiro-ts rejects response → logs ERROR → returns “malformed API response” to extension |
| EF-3 | Network error during continuation | kiro-ts returns timeout/network error → extension may retry |

#### 3.1.3 Business Rules

| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| --- | --- | --- |
| BR-1 | tool\_use\_id from Kiro Q API response MUST be used verbatim — no transformation, re-encoding, or regeneration | BRD Story 2 |
| BR-2 | The same tool\_use\_id value MUST appear in: (a) SSE stream to client, (b) conversation history, (c) expected in continuation from client | BRD Story 1, AC-1,2 |
| BR-3 | tool\_use\_id must be non-empty string matching pattern tooluse\_[A-Za-z0-9]+ | BRD Validation Rules |
| BR-4 | A tool\_use\_id MUST NOT be reused across different tool invocations within a conversation | BRD Validation Rules |
| BR-5 | When multiple tool\_use blocks exist in one response, each block’s ID is independent and all must be preserved | BRD Story 1, AC-4 |
| BR-6 | If a toolResult.toolUseId does not match any history entry, the system MUST log a diagnostic warning (not silently skip) | BRD Story 3 |

#### 3.1.4 Data Specifications

**Input Data (from Kiro Q API Response):**

| Field | Type | Required | Validation | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| content[].type | String | Y | Must be “tool\_use” | Identifies content block as tool invocation |
| content[].id | String | Y | Non-empty, matches tooluse\_[A-Za-z0-9]+ | The tool\_use\_id to preserve |
| content[].name | String | Y | Non-empty | Tool name being invoked |
| content[].input | JSON Object | Y | Valid JSON | Parameters for the tool |

**Output Data (SSE Stream to Extension):**

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| type | String | “content\_block\_start” or “content\_block\_delta” |
| content\_block.type | String | “tool\_use” |
| content\_block.id | String | MUST equal input content[].id — the preserved tool\_use\_id |
| content\_block.name | String | Tool name (passthrough) |
| content\_block.input | JSON Object | Tool parameters (passthrough) |

**Input Data (Continuation Request from Extension):**

| Field | Type | Required | Validation | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| toolResult.toolUseId | String | Y | Must match a stored tool\_use\_id | Correlates result to invocation |
| toolResult.content | String/JSON | Y | Non-empty | Result of tool execution |
| toolResult.isError | Boolean | N | Default: false | Whether tool execution failed |

#### 3.1.5 UI Specifications

Not applicable — this is a backend service fix with no direct UI changes. The Chat Panel UI behavior remains unchanged; only the underlying data flow is corrected.

#### 3.1.6 API Contract (Functional View)

**Endpoint:** POST /chat/completions (internal kiro-ts handler) **Purpose:** Handle chat requests with tool-calling capability

**Input Parameters:**

| Parameter | Type | Required | Business Rule | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| messages[] | Array | Y | — | Conversation history from extension |
| tools[] | Array | N | — | Available tool definitions |
| toolResult.toolUseId | String | Y (on continuation) | BR-2 | Must match previously streamed tool\_use\_id |
| toolResult.content | String | Y (on continuation) | — | Tool execution result |

**Output Data (SSE stream):**

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| event: content\_block\_start | SSE Event | Signals new content block (text or tool\_use) |
| data.content\_block.id | String | tool\_use\_id — MUST match Kiro Q API original (BR-1) |
| data.content\_block.name | String | Tool name |
| event: content\_block\_delta | SSE Event | Incremental tool input data |
| event: message\_stop | SSE Event | End of response |

**Business Error Scenarios:**

| Scenario | User Message | Trigger Condition |
| --- | --- | --- |
| tool\_use\_id not found in history | “Tool continuation failed: tool\_use\_id ‘{id}’ not found in conversation history. Available IDs: […]” | Extension sends toolResult with ID that doesn’t match any stored history entry (BR-6) |
| Malformed API response (no ID) | “Received malformed tool\_use response from API (missing id field)” | Kiro Q API returns tool\_use block without id field |
| Empty tool\_use\_id | “Invalid tool\_use\_id: value cannot be empty” | API returns empty string for tool\_use\_id |

### 3.2 Feature: Improved Error Diagnostics

**Source:** BRD Story 3 — Improve Error Diagnostics for Tool Continuation Failures

#### 3.2.1 Description

When a tool\_use\_id mismatch occurs (whether due to a regression or external factors), the system must provide actionable diagnostic information rather than a generic 400 error.

#### 3.2.2 Use Case: Diagnostic Error on Mismatch

**Use Case ID:** UC-2 **Actor:** Developer (debugging) **Preconditions:** A tool\_use\_id mismatch has occurred **Postconditions:** Developer has sufficient information to diagnose the issue

**Main Flow:**

| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 |  | Extension sends continuation with mismatched toolUseId | ID doesn’t exist in history |
| 2 |  | kiro-ts searches history for matching ID | No match found |
| 3 |  | kiro-ts logs WARNING with: received ID, all stored IDs, conversation turn number | Structured log entry |
| 4 |  | kiro-ts returns descriptive error response to extension | Error includes mismatch details |
| 5 | Developer sees error in Chat Panel |  | Error message explains what went wrong |

**Alternative Flows:**

| ID | Condition | Steps |
| --- | --- | --- |
| AF-1 | Partial match (prefix matches but suffix differs) | Log includes “possible near-match: {id}” to aid debugging |

**Exception Flows:**

| ID | Condition | Steps |
| --- | --- | --- |
| EF-1 | History is empty (no tool\_use ever stored) | Log “conversation history is empty — tool\_use was never stored” |

#### 3.2.3 Business Rules

| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| --- | --- | --- |
| BR-7 | Diagnostic log MUST include: received toolUseId, all stored tool\_use\_ids, conversation turn number | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-8 | Error response to extension MUST say “tool\_use\_id not found in conversation history” — not generic “400 Bad Request” | BRD Story 3, AC-2 |
| BR-9 | Diagnostic logging must be at WARN level (not ERROR) since this is a recoverable client-side issue | Best practice |

## 4. Data Model

### 4.1 Entity Relationship Diagram

This fix does not introduce new persistent storage. All data is in-memory during a conversation session.

### 4.2 Logical Entities

#### Entity: ConversationMessage (in-memory)

| Attribute | Type | Required | Business Rule | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| role | Enum(user, assistant, tool\_result) | Y | — | Message sender role |
| content | Vec | Y | — | Message content blocks |
| turn\_number | u32 | Y | — | Sequential turn counter |

#### Entity: ContentBlock (in-memory)

| Attribute | Type | Required | Business Rule | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| block\_type | Enum(text, tool\_use, tool\_result) | Y | — | Type of content |
| id | Option | Y (for tool\_use) | BR-1, BR-3 | The tool\_use\_id — preserved from API |
| name | Option | Y (for tool\_use) | — | Tool name |
| input | Option | Y (for tool\_use) | — | Tool parameters |
| content | Option | Y (for text/tool\_result) | — | Text or result content |
| tool\_use\_id | Option | Y (for tool\_result) | BR-2 | References which tool\_use this result belongs to |

**Relationships:**

| From Entity | To Entity | Cardinality | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| ConversationMessage | ContentBlock | 1:N | Each message contains one or more content blocks |
| ContentBlock (tool\_result) | ContentBlock (tool\_use) | 1:1 | Each tool\_result references exactly one tool\_use via tool\_use\_id |

## 5. Integration Specifications

### 5.1 External System: Kiro Q API

| Attribute | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Purpose | Provides LLM inference with tool-calling capability |
| Direction | Bidirectional |
| Data Format | JSON (HTTP request/response) |
| Frequency | Real-time (per chat message) |

**Data Exchange:**

| Our Data | External Data | Direction | Business Rule |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Formatted messages array | messages[] (Kiro Q format) | Send | Convert from Anthropic format to Kiro Q format |
| tool\_use content block | content[].id + name + input | Receive | BR-1: Preserve id value exactly |
| tool\_result with matching ID | tool\_result referencing tool\_use\_id | Send | BR-2: ID in result must match stored ID |

### 5.2 External System: VS Code Extension (Client)

| Attribute | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Purpose | Chat Panel UI — sends requests, receives streaming responses |
| Direction | Bidirectional |
| Data Format | SSE (Server-Sent Events) for responses, JSON for requests |
| Frequency | Real-time (per user interaction) |

**Data Exchange:**

| Our Data | External Data | Direction | Business Rule |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| SSE content\_block events | tool\_use\_id + name + input | Send | BR-1, BR-2: ID in stream must match API original |
| Continuation request | toolResult.toolUseId + content | Receive | BR-2: Extension sends back the ID we streamed |

## 6. Processing Logic

### 6.1 Response Conversion (Kiro Q → Streaming)

**Trigger:** Kiro Q API returns HTTP response with tool\_use content blocks **Input:** Raw Kiro Q API JSON response **Output:** SSE events streamed to extension + conversation history entry

**Processing Steps:**

| Step | Description | Error Handling |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Parse Kiro Q response JSON | If parse fails: log ERROR, return 500 to client |
| 2 | For each content block where type == “tool\_use”: extract id, name, input | If id is missing/empty: log ERROR, reject response (BR-3) |
| 3 | Create SSE content\_block\_start event with content\_block.id = <original id> | — |
| 4 | Stream tool input as content\_block\_delta events | — |
| 5 | Store assistant message in conversation history with the SAME id value | If storage fails: log ERROR, stream continues but continuation will fail |
| 6 | Send message\_stop event | — |

**Critical Invariant:** At step 3 and step 5, the id value MUST be the exact string from step 2. No new ID generation, no mapping table, no format conversion.

### 6.2 Continuation Processing (Extension → Kiro Q)

**Trigger:** Extension sends continuation request with toolResult **Input:** JSON request with toolResult.toolUseId and toolResult.content **Output:** Formatted request to Kiro Q API

**Processing Steps:**

| Step | Description | Error Handling |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Extract toolResult.toolUseId from continuation request | If missing: return 400 “toolUseId is required” |
| 2 | Search conversation history for matching tool\_use\_id | If not found: log WARN with diagnostic info (BR-6, BR-7), return descriptive error (BR-8) |
| 3 | Construct tool\_result content block referencing the matched tool\_use | — |
| 4 | Append tool\_result to conversation history | — |
| 5 | Build complete messages array for Kiro Q API request | — |
| 6 | Send request to Kiro Q API | If API returns error: forward error to client |

