## 7. Security Requirements

### 7.1 Authentication & Authorization

| Role | Permissions | Screens/Features |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Developer (authenticated) | Read/Write | Chat Panel tool-calling |
| kiro-ts Service | System | Proxy requests to Kiro Q API using service credentials |

No changes to authentication model. The fix is internal to the conversion logic.

### 7.2 Data Sensitivity Classification

| Data Type | Classification | Business Requirement |
| --- | --- | --- |
| tool\_use\_id | Internal | Correlation identifier only — no PII |
| Tool input/output | Internal | May contain file paths or code snippets — already within user’s workspace |
| Conversation history | Internal | Ephemeral in-memory — cleared on session end |

### 7.3 Audit Trail

| Event | Logged Fields | Retention | Business Reason |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| tool\_use\_id mismatch | received\_id, stored\_ids, turn\_number | Session log | Debugging and regression detection |
| tool\_use streamed | tool\_use\_id, tool\_name | Trace log | Performance monitoring |

## 8. Non-Functional Requirements

| Category | Business Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Performance | No additional latency from the fix | Response streaming latency must not increase by more than 1ms |
| Reliability | 100% ID consistency | Every tool\_use\_id must match across all three locations — zero intermittent failures |
| Observability | Trace-level logging at transformation points | tool\_use\_id logged at: (1) API receive, (2) stream emit, (3) history store, (4) continuation match |
| Backward Compatibility | No breaking changes to streaming format | Extension client requires zero changes to work with the fix |
| Concurrency | Thread-safe history access | Multiple concurrent tool\_use blocks within one response must not race on history writes |

## 9. Error Handling (User-Facing)

### 9.1 Error Scenarios

| Scenario | Severity | User Message | Expected Behavior |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| tool\_use\_id mismatch | Warning | “Tool call failed: could not match tool result to conversation. Please try again.” | User can retry the message. Diagnostic info in kiro-ts logs. |
| Malformed API response | Critical | “Received invalid response from AI service. Please retry.” | kiro-ts rejects response, does not corrupt history |
| History storage failure | Critical | “Internal error during tool processing. Please restart chat.” | Session may be corrupted — suggest new session |
| Network timeout to API | Warning | “AI service did not respond in time. Please retry.” | Retryable by user |

### 9.2 Notification Requirements

| Event | Who is Notified | Channel | Timing |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| tool\_use\_id mismatch | Developer | Chat Panel error message | Immediate |
| Repeated mismatches (>3 in session) | Engineering team | kiro-ts application logs | Immediate (log aggregation) |

## 10. Testing Considerations

### 10.1 Test Scenarios

| ID | Scenario | Input | Expected Output | Priority |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| TC-1 | Single tool\_use — ID preserved in stream | API returns tool\_use with id=tooluse\_ABC | SSE stream contains content\_block.id=tooluse\_ABC | High |
| TC-2 | Single tool\_use — ID preserved in history | API returns tool\_use with id=tooluse\_ABC | Conversation history contains tool\_use\_id=tooluse\_ABC | High |
| TC-3 | Continuation matches history | Extension sends toolResult.toolUseId=tooluse\_ABC | kiro-ts finds match in history, constructs valid API request | High |
| TC-4 | Full ReAct loop — no 400 error | Complete flow: chat → tool\_use → tool\_result → continuation | Loop completes successfully, model returns final text | High |
| TC-5 | Multiple tool\_use blocks | API returns 3 tool\_use blocks with different IDs | All 3 IDs preserved independently in stream and history | High |
| TC-6 | Mismatch diagnostic — ID not found | Extension sends toolResult.toolUseId=tooluse\_WRONG | WARN log with received ID + stored IDs; descriptive error returned | Medium |
| TC-7 | Empty tool\_use\_id from API | API returns tool\_use with id="" | kiro-ts rejects, logs ERROR, returns error to client | Medium |
| TC-8 | Missing id field from API | API returns tool\_use without id field | kiro-ts rejects, logs ERROR | Medium |
| TC-9 | Concurrent tool calls | Two tool\_use blocks processed simultaneously | Both IDs stored correctly without race conditions | High |
| TC-10 | Regression — no new ID generation | Converter processes tool\_use response | No calls to ID generation functions (uuid, random, etc.) | High |

